<a href="/user/show/5150360-david-harris">David Harris</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">According to the author of Persian Fiction Reader (<a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/301923.Persian_Fiction_Reader?ac=1&amp;from_search=true&amp;qid=fX9spBAXmU&amp;rank=1'>https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3...</a>), the Costello translation is very close to the Persian. H<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">According to the author of Persian Fiction Reader (<a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/301923.Persian_Fiction_Reader?ac=1&amp;from_search=true&amp;qid=fX9spBAXmU&amp;rank=1">https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/3...</a>), the Costello translation is very close to the Persian. He recommended it as one that can be studied alongside the original Persian text.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
