<div id="review_417957616" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/417957616" />
    <a title="Szplug" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1843184-szplug"><img alt="Szplug" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1395686229p2/1843184.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/417957616?book_show_action=true">Sep 19, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Szplug" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Szplug" href="/user/show/1843184-szplug">Szplug</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781847490698" href="/book/show/3697614-the-blind-owl">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer417957616" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16812669058721288412">Morphantasy, seeped in a maddened, weary bile for the ponderous chains of life set to a skipping needle. It&apos;s definitely an avenue of oscillated measure, rich with aromatic Middle Eastern fusions of sensual stringency exploding with surrealistic buzz-bombs crafted with twentieth-century precision. Lean and yet plush, engrossing, disturbing, but all without harming any actual human beings. Regrets abound at murdering the void in this way—anger out of place, anguish too primed for such a space; pe</span>
  <span id="freeText16812669058721288412" style="display:none">Morphantasy, seeped in a maddened, weary bile for the ponderous chains of life set to a skipping needle. It's definitely an avenue of oscillated measure, rich with aromatic Middle Eastern fusions of sensual stringency exploding with surrealistic buzz-bombs crafted with twentieth-century precision. Lean and yet plush, engrossing, disturbing, but all without harming any actual human beings. Regrets abound at murdering the void in this way—anger out of place, anguish too primed for such a space; perhaps one lacking the tunneled rigor of Western synthesis, blinded elements, earth and fire union, liquid marbled in ichorous umbrage an onrushing current, emolliating, warm, sedate, unto an encompassing perch, towering twenty-one stories above a horizon-spread metropolitan canvas peppered with shimmery light—all lazy lucent pinball motion, silent, shining, shuffling set-pieces of nocturnal theatre—slumped inside the most casual, most comfortable, most heatedly distracted, most pleasurably hydriotaphial of existential roller coasters—happy, planwise, vision-kissed; slyly rueful and meltingly aware in theory, poisedly decompressed as a hushpuppy slipper in practice. A circumcised gnosticism, desert-derived, is brought into the down of this drowner's stereophonic lament: bitter cucumber ends; index finger rituals; unsettling laughter; gerontophobial mirroring; knifed intentions; sinuous assassins and assignations; Joni Mitchell's <i>Blue</i> made rancid and sour from heartless murmurs; death alternately apprehended with the ecstasy of a perfervid lover and the prostrate dread of a petrified subject; it is <i>all</i> in the approach, my dears.<blockquote>
  <i>One for the money, two for the show,<br />Three for the lady dismembered and buried below,<br />Four might be the drunken cops, you'll never know,<br />So might as well down the wine, it's time to go.</i>
</blockquote></span>
  <a data-text-id="16812669058721288412" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


