<div id="review_207584883" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/207584883" />
    <a title="Jayaprakash Satyamurthy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1497559-jayaprakash-satyamurthy"><img alt="Jayaprakash Satyamurthy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1517076488p2/1497559.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/207584883?book_show_action=true">Sep 12, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jayaprakash Satyamurthy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jayaprakash Satyamurthy" href="/user/show/1497559-jayaprakash-satyamurthy">Jayaprakash Satyamurthy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781847490698" href="/book/show/3697614-the-blind-owl">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer207584883" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12238146635009707958">A tortured psyche disintegrating in a self-created maze of mirrors. A devious novel full of sinister doubles and disorienting narrative multiples. A complex kaleidoscopic image is probably the best analogy, as the same half-dozen or so elements are shifted and reflected into successive patterns that are diverse but all variations on the same theme. Powerful and unsettling stuff. I don&apos;t buy the intricate Eastern mysticism interpretation provided on one website; it is what it is. A masterful port</span>
  <span id="freeText12238146635009707958" style="display:none">A tortured psyche disintegrating in a self-created maze of mirrors. A devious novel full of sinister doubles and disorienting narrative multiples. A complex kaleidoscopic image is probably the best analogy, as the same half-dozen or so elements are shifted and reflected into successive patterns that are diverse but all variations on the same theme. Powerful and unsettling stuff. I don't buy the intricate Eastern mysticism interpretation provided on one website; it is what it is. A masterful portrayal of an alienated, obsessed mind in disarray. Yes, the author may well have shared some of that alienation and disarray but that doesn't negate his mastery in finding a structure and technique to capture it. The Blind Owl is meticulous and accurate within its own frame of reference. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12238146635009707958" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


